metadata.title: Piper PA-28 Cherokee
aws::graph::propositions: Piper PA-28 Cherokee Variants 1970-1973
PA-28-235E Cherokee E was introduced in 1971.
PA-28-235E Cherokee E replaced the rear bench seat with separate seats.
PA-28-235E Cherokee E featured improved soundproofing.
PA-28-235E Cherokee E added air conditioning as an option.
PA-28-235F Cherokee F was introduced in 1972.
PA-28-235F Cherokee F was based on the PA-28-235E model.
PA-28-235F Cherokee F featured a tail fillet.
PA-28-235F Cherokee F featured a new instrument panel.
PA-28-235F Cherokee F included minor changes from the previous model.
PA-28-235 Cherokee Charger was first certified on June 9, 1972.
PA-28-235 Cherokee Charger was introduced in 1973.
PA-28-235 Cherokee Charger is a four-place aircraft.
PA-28-235 Cherokee Charger has fixed landing gear.
PA-28-235 Cherokee Charger is a landplane.
PA-28-235 Cherokee Charger is equipped with a Lycoming O-540-B4B5 engine.
The Lycoming O-540-B4B5 engine produces 235 hp (175 kW).
PA-28-235 Cherokee Charger has a gross weight of 3,000 lb (1,361 kg).
PA-28-235 Cherokee Charger features a five inch fuselage extension compared to the 1963 PA-28-235.
PA-28-235 Cherokee Charger has an increased wing span compared to the 1963 PA-28-235.
PA-28-235 Cherokee Charger has a larger horizontal tail compared to the 1963 PA-28-235.
PA-28-235 Cherokee Charger has an increased gross weight compared to the 1963 PA-28-235.
PA-28-235 Cherokee Charger includes other minor changes from the 1963 PA-28-235.
A variant of the Piper PA-28 Cherokee was introduced in 1970.

details: Piper PA-28 Cherokee HAS VARIANT INTRODUCTION YEAR 1970

text:
Introduced in 1970.
PA-28-235E Cherokee E, as PA-28-235D with rear bench seat replaced by separate seats and improved soundproofing.  Air conditioning was added as an option on this variant.  Introduced in 1971.
PA-28-235F Cherokee F, as PA-28-235E with tail fillet, a new instrument panel, and minor changes.  Introduced in 1972.
PA-28-235 Cherokee Charger, four-place, fixed landing gear landplane, Lycoming O-540-B4B5 engine of 235 hp (175 kW), gross weight 3,000 lb (1,361 kg). First certified on June 9, 1972, and introduced in 1973. Changes from the 1963 certified PA-28-235 Cherokee 235 include a five inch fuselage extension, wing span increase, larger horizontal tail, gross weight increase and other minor changes.
